text: Zell im Fichtelgebirge, formerly Zell (official name until July 2007) is a market town in Hof in Bavaria in Germany. == Geography == The center of the market parish is between the towns of Hof and Bayreuth, about 5 km from the B 2 federal road and about 10 km from the A 9 motorway. The River Saale rises on the Waldstein ridge in the Fichtelgebirge near Zell im Fichtelgebirge. == References == Category:Hof (district)
title: Zell im Fichtelgebirge
